snippet.textDisplay:
Does anyone else think that the televised SX production could be better? I couldn't hear a word Chad Reed was saying, when he sat in the Oakland booth. I thought the sound mix was bad when it was on FS1. I hoped it would be better, with NBC. But it isn't. Every week I struggle to make out the dialogue, through the sound of the bikes.
And too often the cameras aren't on a hot battle, while they focus on a big name, running all alone.
